[According to the Thai Ministry of Public Health, Bureau of Epidemiology's (BOE) report of the situation of dengue infection in Thailand, between 1 Jan 2012 and 1 Jul 2012, available in Thai at http://www.boe.moph.go.th/boedb/surdata/disease.php?ds=82, a total of 18 569 cases and 19 deaths were reported nationwide. The attack rate was 29.07 per 100 000 population, with a case fatality rate (CFR) of 0.10 percent. Of these, 8995 cases and no deaths were due to dengue fever (DF); 9187 cases and 10 deaths were due to dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF); and 388 cases and 9 deaths were due to dengue shock syndrome (DSS).

For maps showing Thailand's regions, see http://www.thailand-map.net/thailand_provinces/; for provinces, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Provinces_of_Thailand. For the interactive HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Thailand with links to other recent ProMED-mail and PRO/MBDS postings, see http://healthmap.org/r/1l5W. - Mod.SCM]

